  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining the Application Type**\n\nOkay, I\'ve got a handle on the application\'s nature now, thanks to the `metadata.json` file. It\'s called EAZY BILLING, which is a good starting point. I\'m moving toward identifying key functionalities and core structures to explain it properly. I am aiming to use this information to create a more comprehensive overview for the user.\n\n\n**Pinpointing Technical Specifications**\n\nI am now focusing on the technical specifications. The application, *EAZY BILLING*, is a React-based application using TypeScript and Vite. It utilizes Tailwind CSS for styling and Dexie (IndexedDB) for local storage, syncing with Firebase. There are mobile builds using Capacitor/Android, AI features with the Gemini API, and integrations for QR code generation and scanning, with Supabase referenced, though Firebase appears primary for auth and sync.\n\n\n**Outlining Key Features**\n\nNow I\'m diving deep into the application\'s key features, breaking them down into logical categories: Master Data, Accounting, Reporting, Communication, Operations, and Settings. It\'s becoming clearer how the screens relate to each other functionally. I\'m focusing on the user workflows within each section. The integration of AI for assistance looks really interesting, and I\'m noting the potential in the `AIAssistant.tsx` file. I am also making sure to explore the Nearby Shops screen, with its geolocation functionality using Leaflet. I\'m aiming to provide a complete picture of the application\'s capabilities.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "**Eazy Billing** is a comprehensive, production-grade sales and inventory management application designed for both desktop and mobile (via Capacitor). It functions as an **offline-first** system that syncs in real-time across devices using Firebase.\n\nHere is a breakdown of what the application does and how it\'s built:\n\n### 1. Functional Overview\nThe app is essentially a \"mini-ERP\" system tailored for small to medium businesses. Its features include:\n\n*   **Sales & Invoicing:** Create invoices with real-time calculations. It supports GST, HSN codes, and item-wise taxation.\n*   **Accounting & Finance:** Includes full journal entries, contra entries, payments, and ledger management. It can generate Financial Reports like **Trial Balances, Profit & Loss statements, and Balance Sheets**.\n*   **Inventory (Master) Management:** Manage Items (products), Parties (customers/suppliers), Units (Kg, Pcs), Taxes, and Categories.\n*   **Dynamic Reporting:** Offers detailed reports by Party, by Item, Stock Summaries, and GST-specific reports.\n*   **Communication Hub:** A built-in chat system and broadcast group feature for business communication.\n*   **Operations:** Support for manufacturing processes, staff attendance, and order tracking.\n*   **AI Integration:** Includes an **AI Assistant** (powered by Gemini) to help with tasks like pre-filling items or answering business queries.\n*   **Location Services:** A \"Nearby Shops\" feature using maps (Leaflet) to find or display business locations.\n\n### 2. Technical Stack\n*   **Frontend:** React 19 with TypeScript and Vite.\n*   **Styling:** Tailwind CSS for a responsive, modern UI.\n*   **Database (Offline-First):** Uses **Dexie.js** (a wrapper for IndexedDB) to store all business data locally in the browser/app. This ensures the app works perfectly without an internet connection.\n*   **Backend & Sync:** **Firebase** (Firestore/Auth) handles user login and syncs local Dexie data to the cloud so you can access your bills on multiple devices.\n*   **Mobile Mobile:** **Capacitor** is used to package the web code into a native Android application (found in the `/android` directory).\n*   **AI:** Integrates **Google Gemini API** for smart business automation.\n\n### 3. Key File Structure\n*   **`/components`**: Contains the logic for every screen (e.g., `InvoiceScreen.tsx`, `DashboardScreen.tsx`).\n*   **`/services`**:\n    *   `billingService.ts`: The \"brain\" of the app; handles all local database logic via Dexie.\n    *   `firebaseService.ts`: Manages cloud synchronization and authentication.\n    *   `aiService.ts`: Handles requests to the Gemini AI.\n*   **`App.tsx`**: The main navigation router that manages the global state (theme, language, active Financial Year).\n*   **`types.ts`**: Defines the data models for Invoices, Items, Parties, and Transactions to ensure code safety.\n\n### 4. Advanced Features\n*   **Financial Year (FY) Support:** You can switch between different databases for different financial years.\n*   **Deep Linking:** Supports \"Auto-Import\" via URL (WhatsApp links), allowing users to click a link and immediately import a transaction into their app.\n*   **Security:** Features a `LockScreen` with PIN protection to keep business data private.\n\nIn short, it is a **fast, keyboard-accessible, and highly portable** billing solution that combines the speed of a local app with the reliability of cloud sync."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 3
      nanos: 184184925
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
