  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Firebase Integration**\n\nI\'ve established the application\'s reliance on Firebase. This framework provides the backbone for cloud storage, user authentication, and real-time functionalities such as chat and invoice management.\n\n\n**Detailing API Dependencies**\n\nI\'m now detailing all the API dependencies. Firebase is set up, no further configuration needed. I\'ve noted the need for a `GEMINI_API_KEY` for AI functionalities. Geolocation uses the browser\'s native API; no key is necessary, just user permissions. Maps are handled by Leaflet with OpenStreetMap, so I\'m not using any required API key at present.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "Based on my analysis of your application\'s code and configuration, here are the API keys and setup requirements for your app:\n\n### 1. **Gemini API Key** (Required for AI features)\n*   **Purpose:** Powers the \"AI Assistant\" which allows you to create bills and ask about stock levels using voice or text commands (e.g., \"Add 5 packets of Milk for Rahul\").\n*   **How to get it:**\n    1.  Go to the [Google AI Studio API Key page](https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey).\n    2.  Click **\"Create API key\"**.\n    3.  Copy the key.\n*   **Where to put it:** Open your project settings in this builder and add a new environment variable named `GEMINI_API_KEY` with your key as the value.\n\n### 2. **Firebase Configuration** (Already Configured)\n*   **Purpose:** Handles cloud features like real-time chat between shops, cloud backup, and sharing invoices/payments directly between users.\n*   **Status:** I have already provisioned a Firebase project for you (`liquid-nova-2cf5x`). The necessary configuration is stored in `firebase-applet-config.json`.\n*   **Note:** If you want to use the **Shared Chat** or **Cloud Sync** features, you should enable **\"Anonymous Authentication\"** in the Firebase Console (Authentication > Sign-in method) if it isn\'t already.\n\n### 3. **Device Permissions** (No keys needed)\nYour app requires access to certain hardware features. Users will be prompted for these:\n*   **Location:** Used in the \"Nearby Shops\" feature to find and connect with suppliers or customers near you.\n*   **Camera:** Used for the QR Code scanner to quickly scan item codes or party IDs.\n*   **Microphone:** Used for the AI Voice command feature.\n\n### 4. **Maps (Leaflet)**\n*   **Status:** The application uses **OpenStreetMap** through the Leaflet library. This is a free service and **does not require an API key**.\n\n### Summary of what you need to do:\n1. Get a **Gemini API Key** from [AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey).\n2. Add it to your project environment variables as `GEMINI_API_KEY`.\n3. When using the app, ensure you allow **Location** and **Camera** permissions when requested by the browser.\n\nWould you like me to help you integrate any other services, or troubleshoot any specific feature?"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 1
      nanos: 900275209
    }
